HEADWORD: Amboyna wood
<hw>Am*boy"na wood</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>A beautiful mottled and
curled wood, used in cabinetwork. It is obtained from the
<spn>Pterocarpus Indicus</spn> of Amboyna, Borneo, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

